        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> .. seeing as how this is a bit of a global community.  ^^</P><P>Just wanted to say hi and greetings to the Necromancer community here.  Been playing since retail release, and I've played a couple of Necromancers in that time... though I never really played them past 20 or so.  Not because I didn't like the class, but because my guild at the time "needed" other classes.  But I've long since left that guild and server behind.  Currently playing on Lanys T`vyl, started a Necromancer recently to pair with a Magician, simply because I've always loved the pet classes.  With all the fixes recently, I figured "why not"?  Planning on taking both to 60... and it's nice to see a dedicated community forum like this one.  Created a dark elven necromancer, not for stats or faction, per se, but simply because I adore the new dark elf graphics.  Pleased to have found a forum where I can come to ask questions about situations she'll run across, and toss ideas around about the class in general.   Although I've noticed that occasionally, questions about the game or how to pull CampXYZ get met with some venom from a few people here.</P><P>A few questions, as I recently started EQ again after quitting just prior the big changes that have taken place over the last few months.  I quit, they fix things.  Hmmm.  Perhaps I should quit again and they'd give Necromancers back the old skelly models, offer a no-spectre illusion option for our final lich-line spell, and completely revise the Necromancer AAXP list.  But that's another topic.  Or three.  I've found conflicting information on these questions, so if I could get answers, I'd apprecate it.  ^^</P><P>First, are our pets ALL the same until EoT?  White bone?  Same size?</P><P>Second, are our pets always summoned at max level?</P><P>Third, was the DoT nerf removed... ie: moving mobs now take full damage from DoTs?  Also, I never really tested post-nerf... did DoTs do full damage if a mob was feared?</P><P>Fourth, if you're in a group, and ANYONE in the group does any damage to the mob, does the pet take XP?</P><P>Sorry if these questions were asked already, but I know they botched the pet patches at first, and had to repatch them... so existing threads, I've noticed, are sometimes wrong with information simply because they were posted before the patch-fixes were implemented.</P><P> </font></td>

